<TEXT>
THE world body of athletics, desperate to beef up the star-starved
World Indoor championships in Barcelona, was struck another blow
yesterday when leading 3000m runner Venuste Niyongabo of Burundi was
deported.
Even more embarrassing than their mishandling of the 60m -- Linford
Christie will not run on a wild card -- was their failure to supply a
promised visa at the airport. Niyongabo was deported to Rome and will
not run.
