<TEXT>
ST MIRREN have rallied round to help their fans who travelled for last
week's abandoned first division match against Stranraer. The club will
pay for the six buses which took their supporters to Stair Park.
Tomorrow St Mirren again head for Stair Park and, as the fans did not
get their money back when last week's match was cancelled at half-time,
Stranraer have decided to allow them in free.
* ARSONISTS set fire to the car of Fiorentina defender Gianluca Luppi
outside his home in Florence yesterday. The motive was not clear, but it
follows the Italian team's 8-2 hammering by Lazio.
* WIMBLEDON manager Joe Kinnear has agreed to a voluntary touchline
ban until his appearance before the FA over recent comments about
referees.
