<HEADLINE>Lawrie on the move</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>JOSEPH DILLON</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>46</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979468455</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SUE Lawrie, the Scotland and Great Britain's goalkeeper who switched
her allegiance at the start of the season from second division Ealing to
Slough, is on the move again, this time to Boroughmuir.
Lawrie's initial transfer proved a disaster, because she was injured
at a Great Britain training camp in August and missed the start of
Slough's campaign. When she was fit again, Sue Knight had taken her
place and performed so well that she was promoted to the England squad.
During her five months at Slough Lawrie started only one league match
and was substitute in two others, including a cup-tie. Yesterday she
admitted: ''In order to continue my international career I had to
move.''
Lawrie will be a tremendous asset to Boroughmuir in their struggle to
avoid relegation. However, she is unlikely to gather any points
tomorrow, when Edinburgh Ladies are their opponents.
</TEXT>
