<HEADLINE>Boost for Menzieshill</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>46</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979468456</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
MENZIESHILL, Scotland's representatives next season in the European
Men's Indoor Club championship, this week received the welcome news that
they will encounter only one German side in the finals.
Rot Weiss Cologne, the reigning champions, regained their national
title with an 8-7 victory over Havestehuder, with Durkheimer taking
third place following their 14-12 defeat of European outdoor champions
Uhlenhorst in what has gone down as one of the greatest contests ever
seen in the German championship.
Indeed, if the European Hockey Federation continues with its normal
draw procedure Menzieshill, thanks to MIM winning the B Division last
month, will be seeded No.7 and will go into the opposite group from
Cologne along with the national champions of Poland, Czech Republic, and
Spain.
</TEXT>
