<HEADLINE>Birdies that got away</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>46</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979468462</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ULSTERMAN Darren Clarke was joint leader after the first round of the
Malaysian Open in Kuala Lumpur -- but missed out on setting a new course
record.
Clarke had opportunities to take the outright lead and break the
Templer Park Country Club course record of 66. However, he missed five
birdie putts in succession from the thirteenth to seventeenth and
finished on five-under-par 67 to share the lead with Canada's Jim
Rutledge. Leading scores:
