<TEXT>
Grozny, Thursday
RUSSIAN artillery pounded separatist Chechen villages today despite a
local truce and a public promise by President Boris Yeltsin to seek a
political settlement.
Refugees poured out of the Achkhoi-Martan district west of the
devastated Chechen capital Grozny and said the Russians were still
firing on settlements. White flags fluttered from their ramshackle
convoys.
In Moscow, Yeltsin told three European foreign ministers he intended
to resolve the Chechnya conflict through negotiations -- 12 weeks after
sending troops to crush the region's three-year-old independence
bid.--Reuter.
</TEXT>
