<DATE>950310</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Murder case Briton guilty</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979468561</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
OSLO: A 32-year-old British citizen yesterday was convicted of
murdering a gay former doctor by stabbing him at least 20 times, the
Norwegian news agency NTB reported. Throughout the four-day trial in
Oslo Superior Court, Christopher Kirby maintained his innocence, saying
he had been to the Norwegian's apartment but did not remember stabbing
him.
The body of Tage Ansethmoen, 34, was found in his Oslo apartment on
November 23, 1991, shortly after he was paroled from prison. The former
doctor had been sentenced for the attempted murder of an 81-year-old
woman. The court was expected to sentence Kirby today, said NTB.
</TEXT>
