<TEXT>
FORMER procurator-fiscal Fergus Brown, lover of Dixieland jazz and
military music, picked up a conductor's baton for the first time and put
the band of HM Royal Marines Scotland through its paces at the Carnegie
Hall in Dumfermline. The former Marine and self-confessed closet
clarinettist won a competition to conduct part of the band's last
concert of the season and he led them through the second half of the
show. Yesterday his audience was reduced to his dog Monty for a
performance near Mr Brown's Peebles home.
</TEXT>
