<TEXT>
The Queen's first visit to Northern Ireland since the IRA ceasefire
began was greeted by large crowds who braved the freezing temperatures
to welcome her. During the day-long visit she met Roman Catholic Primate
Cardinal Cahal Daly -- who challenged Ireland's Catholics to put aside
their old doubts and suspicions at a time of exciting opportunities.
